    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="512"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/893.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Smith</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 19. Please confer with Haitian Government as to the desirability of
                    Consul at Cape Haitien making trip suggested by Theodore and Minister Zamor. If
                    it is desired that he proceed, instructions will be sent by Navy Department to
                    Commander of <hi rend="italic">Nashville</hi>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
